# EscapeZoom Business Domain (theory & rules)

## 1. Inventory & Slot
- **Unit of sale:** One slot = one game, one date+time.
- **Anti-collision:** Slot becomes reserved on payment; no double booking.
- **Temporary lock:** e.g. 15 minutes from click (reserve intent).
- **Slot states:** available, reserved, blocked, cancelled.
- **Working day:** e.g. 08:00–07:59 next day.

## 2. Pricing
- **Calendar:** Normal vs holiday/weekend.
- **Capacity:** Base price for minimum players; extra amount per additional person.
- **Last-minute discount:** If not booked X hours before start.
- **Payment type at checkout:** Deposit vs full.

## 3. Commission & shares
- **Platform commission:** Item amount × (commission % / 100); per-game configurable.
- **Venue owner share:** After commission.
- **Wallet share at checkout:** e.g. prepaid minus (online paid + coupon + level discount); non-negative.

## 4. Points & Levels
- **Points for:** booking, comment, collection, like, registration, profile completion.
- **Levels 1–4:** By point thresholds (e.g. up to 150→1, 700→2, 7000→3, above→4).
- **Level discount at checkout:** e.g. 5% and 10% for level 3 and 4.
- **Rating power:** Depends on level.
- **Feature access:** Collection, invitation, like, bio, avatar — by level and caps.

## 5. Wallet & Settlements
- **Wallet:** Deposit, withdraw, use in purchase.
- **Transaction states:** pending, completed, rejected.
- **Settlement:** One active settlement request per user/owner; flow: request → approve → pay owner.

## 6. Rating & Satisfaction
- **Who can rate:** Only user who completed a booking for that game.
- **Product satisfaction:** From approved comments (count, positive, average).
- **Order satisfaction:** Yes/no/neutral after experience.

## 7. Badges & Lists
- **Hottest:** Quality of comments (e.g. Bayesian) + recent views; comment weight by level; penalty products excluded.
- **Topsale:** Real bookings in period (e.g. 30 days); statuses completed/held/partial; higher-level users weight more; penalty applied.
- **Popular:** Clicks/views in period.
- **Full list:** Merge e.g. hottest + newest.

## 8. Cancellation
- **Who:** Customer or owner can request.
- **Statuses:** pending, approved, rejected, cancelled, expired.
- **Audit:** Log every action.
- **On approve:** Slot becomes available again; parties and finances updated as needed.

## 9. Checkout & validation
- **Preconditions:** User logged in; slot not expired; slot still available and not locked by another.
- **Before place order:** Validate slot still available, minimum amount, other rules.
- **Coupon:** One per order; can restrict to users or first purchase; block coupon if product has special discount; discount by type (percent or fixed).

## 10. Notifications
- **Confirm booking:** Right after payment (e.g. SMS).
- **Reminder:** X time before slot (e.g. 3 h).
- **After slot end:** Send link/message for review.
- **Delivery:** Use queue for retry and load.

## 11. Game attributes (filter/display)
- Genre, style, difficulty (1–10), age limit, duration, location (city, area, neighbourhood).

## 12. Game comments
- **Who:** Only buyer with completed order for that game.
- **Window:** From 90 minutes after slot start until 1 week.
- **One comment per user per game ever** (even if bought multiple times).
- **Missed window:** New purchase gives a new chance (90 min after that slot start, up to 1 week).
- **Storage:** Dedicated game-reviews store (not WordPress comments).
- **Admin:** Separate section "Game reviews" reads from that store.

## 13. Game rating
- **Source:** Computed from valid (published, counted) comments.
- **Delete/hide comment:** Remove its effect from rating.
- **Re-add/unhide comment:** Restore its effect.

## 14. Identities & relations
- **Brand:** Separate entity; every game must belong to one brand.
- **City:** One per game.
- **Area:** Game can be in multiple areas of one city.
- **Genre, Theme/Style, Tag:** Multiple per game.

## 15. Brand fields
- Name, description, score (average of linked games), featured image, team members (name, photo, role), list of games linked.

## 16. Game fields (full)
- **Core:** name, short intro, scenario, rules, short link (like Woo short link), banner/featured image, gallery (optional).
- **Booking:** Booking info (like previous system), sales box (sale status, dropdown, owner, session manager, second mobile).
- **Meta:** Game level (labels match frontend), age limit (dropdown 8–20).
- **Cinema/terror show type:** Display type, seat type, safety level, player count, game duration (minutes).
- **Location:** Full address with map (pick on map → auto-fill editable; or type address → pin on map); neighbourhood; lat/long stored (map can fill; UI may hide).
- **Other:** Amenities (text list, no link/id), mobile numbers (repeater), embed video code (repeater, nice display).
